http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/Bharathiraaja-son-team-up-for-new-Tamil-film/article13986328.ece

Actor Mahat Raghavendra will play the lead in a yet-untitled Tamil project, which will be directed by actor Manoj Bharathi and produced by his father and veteran filmmaker Bharathiraaja.“This is going to be a very interesting project. It’s such an honour to be working with Bharathiraaja sir, who will be producing this film while son Manoj will direct it,” Mahat told IANS.He also added that the regular shooting of the project will start from March.Without divulging much information, Mahat said the film will remain very special in his career.Mahat, meanwhile, is currently busy shooting for Telugu film “She”.